This paper deals with fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses computational challenges and algorithms, which could place it in the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with auditing and learning fair classifiers, which could place it in the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
